body:
This is part of the logic that generates a separate jar file as a way to configure classpath that are too long to pass on the command line.

@rsalvador I'm curious which JDK you're using, is it newer than JDK 8? The long term plan here is to replace this logic in the stub template with an `@argument` file: https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_java/issues/331

(I'm also not sure why the stub template generates this every time it's executed, instead of having Bazel create a separate action that generates the separate jar file once; that came up in https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/19036.)
